verses.text: Hear ye this, O house of Jacob , which are called by the name of Israel , and are come forth out of the waters of Judah , which swear by the name of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and make mention of the God of Israel , \add but\add* not in truth , nor in righteousness.
For they call themselves of the holy city , and stay themselves upon the God of Israel ; The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* of hosts \add is\add* his name.
I have declared the former things from the beginning ; and they went forth out of my mouth , and I shewed them; I did \add them\add* suddenly , and they came to pass.
Because I knew that thou \add art\add* obstinate , and thy neck \add is\add* an iron sinew , and thy brow brass ;\f + \fr 48.4 \ft obstinate: Heb. hard\f*

I have even from the beginning declared \add it\add* to thee; before it came to pass I shewed \add it\add* thee: lest thou shouldest say , Mine idol hath done them, and my graven image , and my molten image , hath commanded them.
Thou hast heard , see all this; and will not ye declare \add it\add*? I have shewed thee new things from this time , even hidden things , and thou didst not know them.
They are created now, and not from the beginning; even before the day when thou heardest them not; lest thou shouldest say , Behold, I knew them.

Yea, thou heardest not; yea, thou knewest not; yea, from that time \add that\add* thine ear was not opened : for I knew that thou wouldest deal very treacherously , and wast called a transgressor from the womb. \p
¶ For my name’s sake will I defer mine anger , and for my praise will I refrain for thee, that I cut thee not off.
Behold, I have refined thee, but not with silver ; I have chosen thee in the furnace of affliction.\f + \fr 48.10 \ft with…: or, for silver\f*
For mine own sake, \add even\add* for mine own sake, will I do \add it:\add* for how should \add my name\add* be polluted ? and I will not give my glory unto another. \p
¶ Hearken unto me, O Jacob and Israel , my called ; I \add am\add* he; I \add am\add* the first , I also \add am\add* the last.

Mine hand also hath laid the foundation of the earth , and my right hand hath spanned the heavens : \add when\add* I call unto them, they stand up together.\f + \fr 48.13 \ft my…: or, the palm of my right hand hath spread out\f*

All ye, assemble yourselves, and hear ; which among them hath declared these \add things\add*? The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath loved him: he will do his pleasure on Babylon , and his arm \add shall be on\add* the Chaldeans.
I, \add even\add* I, have spoken ; yea, I have called him: I have brought him, and he shall make his way prosperous. \p

¶ Come ye near unto me, hear ye this; I have not spoken in secret from the beginning ; from the time that it was, there \add am\add* I: and now the Lord \nd \+w GOD|strong="H3069"\+w*\nd*, and his Spirit , hath sent me.

Thus saith the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, thy Redeemer , the Holy One of Israel ; I \add am\add* the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* thy God which teacheth thee to profit , which leadeth thee by the way \add that\add* thou shouldest go.
O that thou hadst hearkened to my commandments ! then had thy peace been as a river , and thy righteousness as the waves of the sea :
Thy seed also had been as the sand , and the offspring of thy bowels like the gravel thereof; his name should not have been cut off nor destroyed from before me. \p

¶ Go ye forth of Babylon , flee ye from the Chaldeans , with a voice of singing declare ye, tell this, utter it \add even\add* to the end of the earth ; say ye, The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* hath redeemed his servant Jacob.
And they thirsted not \add when\add* he led them through the deserts : he caused the waters to flow out of the rock for them: he clave the rock also, and the waters gushed out.
\add There is\add* no peace , saith the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, unto the wicked.
